            <div class="brand-section" id="ferrari">
                <h2>Ferrari</h2>
                <img src="https://source.unsplash.com/800x400/?ferrari" alt="Ferrari">
                <p>Ferrari is an Italian luxury sports car manufacturer known for its high-performance vehicles and rich racing heritage. Founded by Enzo Ferrari in 1939, the company originally started as Auto Avio Costruzioni before transitioning into the Ferrari brand we know today. Ferrari's cars are often associated with exclusivity, cutting-edge technology, and breathtaking speed.</p>
                <p>The prancing horse logo, derived from a World War I flying ace’s emblem, has become one of the most recognizable symbols in the automotive world. The company’s signature color, Rosso Corsa (racing red), is deeply tied to its motorsport dominance. Ferrari has been a dominant force in Formula 1, winning multiple championships and developing groundbreaking innovations in aerodynamics and engine performance.</p>
                <p>Ferrari’s model lineup includes legendary cars like the Ferrari 488, LaFerrari, and SF90 Stradale, all designed for speed and luxury. Limited production models like the Ferrari Enzo and Ferrari F40 have made Ferrari an icon among collectors. The brand’s commitment to engineering excellence ensures every Ferrari provides a thrilling driving experience.</p>
